gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 130, Wizards 121
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Anthony Edwards career-high 51 points (6-13 3pt. FG), the Timberwolves defeated the Wizards, 130-121. Edwards added six rebounds and seven assists for the Timberwolves, while Nickeil Alexander-Walker added 23 points, four rebounds and five assists in the victory. Corey Kispert (25 points, five assists, five 3PM) and Jordan Poole (24 points, six assists, five 3PM) combined for 49 points for the Wizards in the losing effort. The Timberwolves have won back-to-back games as they improve to 55-24 on the season, while the Wizards fall to 15-65.
